Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on ultra-reliable and low-latency communications in vehicular networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning-based approach for beam tracking. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper modifies classical control theory methods for non-stationary scenarios. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with packet delay and channel information. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for beam tracking.
